- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is likely because the paper deals with the concept of cographs and uniformly non-prime 2-structures, which are combinatorial objects.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely because the paper involves the construction of algorithms to derive species trees from gene trees, which can be seen as a type of machine learning problem.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possibility because the paper deals with reconciling gene trees and species trees, which can be seen as a type of game between different evolutionary events.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility because the paper involves the development of computational methods to analyze evolutionary events.
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possibility because the paper deals with the organization and analysis of large amounts of genetic data.
